1
00:00:07,090 --> 00:00:18,600
Thank you, Betty. Good morning. We continue in this series on worship. And so for a few moments, I'm going to be talking about praise and worship.

2
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:27,280
And then we're going to continue by singing and praising and worshiping. We welcome you to be a part of that this morning. God bless you all as we gather.

3
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:36,280
I want to share a short story. There were two young newlyweds preparing to enjoy their very first baked ham dinner in their new apartment.

4
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:38,880
You can just imagine what that's all about.

5
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:42,360
And after unwrapping the meat and setting it on the cutting board,

6
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:46,840
the young bride, she chopped off both ends of the ham, just like that,

7
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:49,160
and threw the pieces away.

8
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:56,160
And the mystified young husband said, why did you do that?

9
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:58,660
She said, I don't know.

10
00:00:58,740 --> 00:00:59,780
My mother always did.

11
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:03,290
Maybe it helps bring out the flavor.

12
00:01:05,380 --> 00:01:08,400
Well, the husband was not satisfied with that answer,

13
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,540
and so he immediately called his mother-in-law,

14
00:01:10,540 --> 00:01:16,360
got her on the phone and said can you tell me why you would cut off the ends of the ham before you

15
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:21,680
cook it and she said well i'm i'm not really sure that's just the way my mother used to do it and

16
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:29,880
it was always delicious well as soon as he hung up with her he called grandma grandma we've got a

17
00:01:29,880 --> 00:01:36,050
very important question for you can you tell us why you kept cutting off the ends of a ham before

18
00:01:36,050 --> 00:01:43,900
you cook it. She said, oh, yes, my dear. In her quiet, thin voice, I cut the ends of the ham off

19
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:58,240
so it would fit in my pan. Traditions. Traditions can be so wonderful. They can minister to us.

20
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:05,340
They can speak to us. They can enrich us. But they can also become, over time, without careful

21
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:15,880
attention, lifeless forms that lose their meaning. Worshiping the living God is an act that our

22
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:22,840
bodies and souls can lift our spirits and connect with God Most High. But forms of worship, if we're

23
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:33,950
not careful, can become hollow and usual and even dead. In the current evangelical church today,

24
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:42,110
Worship has often been boiled down to, in what one person has said, a few songs and a lecture.

25
00:02:44,110 --> 00:02:46,210
Is there more?

26
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,060
That's the question.

27
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:55,560
If God is the audience and we are the participants and the worship leaders are the prompters,

28
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:58,360
can we offer God more?

29
00:02:59,660 --> 00:03:01,160
It's an important question.

30
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:06,320
A.W. Tozer, great writer of our last century, said,

31
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:11,740
Worship is the missing jewel of the evangelical church.

32
00:03:12,980 --> 00:03:13,760
Strong statement.

33
00:03:15,850 --> 00:03:17,850
Similarly, theologian Karl Barth said,

34
00:03:17,850 --> 00:03:27,090
Christian worship is the most momentous, the most urgent, the most glorious action that can take place in human life.

35
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,250
I think Barth is right.

36
00:03:32,860 --> 00:03:35,240
But do we live like this?

37
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:39,900
It's one thing to see it in words and to nod our heads.

38
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:48,660
It's another to live as if worship was truly the most momentous, urgent, glorious action that we can ever participate in.

39
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:52,580
Do we live as his people to worship?

40
00:03:53,660 --> 00:04:00,380
Do we expectantly come to church to gather with God's people and expect God to receive our worship

41
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:03,700
and for God to speak to you and change you?

42
00:04:03,940 --> 00:04:06,400
Is that the attitude with which we come?

43
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:10,370
And I have to confess, over the years, that hasn't been my attitude.

44
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:18,620
The Bible says, let everything that has breath praise the Lord.

45
00:04:19,970 --> 00:04:22,090
Let everything that has breath praise the Lord.

46
00:04:22,410 --> 00:04:28,310
Is that our heart's cry that we say, yes, Lord, let everything that has breath praise the Lord?

47
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:37,380
I'd like to share a few words from an author in Discipleship Journal a few issues back.

48
00:04:37,580 --> 00:04:43,290
The author writes, the experience of the presence of God in worship and praise

49
00:04:43,290 --> 00:04:47,870
is readily available to all who know Jesus Christ.

50
00:04:48,350 --> 00:04:52,880
Yet most of us, the writer says, fail to enter into his presence.

51
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:57,660
We often come away from corporate worship never touching him.

52
00:04:58,620 --> 00:05:02,180
Even our private times of quietness in the word and in prayer

53
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:05,200
fail to bring us into the holy place.

54
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:08,240
Our worship degenerates into ritual

55
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:12,120
and our spiritual lives become arid and lifeless.

56
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:15,020
Like the majority of the people in that sanctuary,

57
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:20,300
we miss the quieting presence of God in the midst of our praise and our worship.

58
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:26,130
But I don't know how to praise, one man admitted during an evening Bible study.

59
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:32,300
I didn't grow up as a Christian, and praise has not been a part of my life all these years.

60
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:35,220
I just don't have any experience.

61
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:39,960
But then when the home team scores a touchdown,

62
00:05:40,930 --> 00:05:46,650
That same man jumps out of his chair, yelling and cheering and screaming at the TV set.

63
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:54,790
And to anyone who asks, he will give a glowing account of the merits of the woman that he married.

64
00:05:55,740 --> 00:06:00,800
And even those who don't ask are regaled with the exploits of their new grandson.

65
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:04,400
We do know how to praise.

66
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:06,900
We praise our diets.

67
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,120
We praise our cars.

68
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:13,620
We praise our VCRs and DVDs and subwoofers and surround sound.

69
00:06:13,980 --> 00:06:15,780
We praise all these things.

70
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:25,260
We extol the value and the virtues of the things we most cherish in life.

71
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:31,490
Yet, the author says, we need to learn how to praise God.

72
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,580
What is praise?

73
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,080
What is praise?

74
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:42,840
Praise is the act of expressing your gratitude, your admiration, your commendation.

75
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:50,020
It's a way of giving your applause to something that you value, that you find great and wonderful.

76
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:54,930
And when your home team scores the touchdown, we praise them.

77
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:01,990
I'll never forget one time studying as a high school kid.

78
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:09,650
And for some reason I was busily working on an exam coming up and my father was watching the 49ers.

79
00:07:09,770 --> 00:07:10,530
It was the 80s.

80
00:07:10,590 --> 00:07:11,610
They were on that roll.

81
00:07:12,030 --> 00:07:15,710
And it was that Joe Montana starting from the one-yard line all the way to the end.

82
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:18,950
And I was so busy in chemistry, I just couldn't watch the game.

83
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:24,590
And my father is screaming and jumping and leaping about the living room.

84
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:26,030
Scared me.

85
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,980
Never seen my father act this way before.

86
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,780
He was into it.

87
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:33,940
And they won, praise the Lord, for you Niner fans.

88
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:35,840
None here, I guess.

89
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:36,380
Just me.

90
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:36,840
Oh, okay.

91
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:37,220
Thank you.

92
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:37,600
Thank you.

93
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:44,060
You see, we know how to praise the things that we love and that make us excited.

94
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:48,710
For some reason, though, we come to church and we squelch all of that.

95
00:07:50,030 --> 00:07:56,260
And yet, if God is the thing we love the most, can we not give him praise and glory and honor?

96
00:08:00,570 --> 00:08:07,620
There are three outcomes, not only of corporate praise, but also a lifestyle of praise in your personal life.

97
00:08:07,980 --> 00:08:08,960
I'd like to share them with you.

98
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:16,580
Number one, the habit of praise, the repetitive process of giving God praise, it renews our faith.

99
00:08:17,590 --> 00:08:18,550
It renews our faith.

100
00:08:19,350 --> 00:08:26,190
Praise keeps God's grace in Jesus Christ fresh and vivid in front of our eyes.

101
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:35,180
You've seen, friends, how muscles grow stronger when you exercise them, right?

102
00:08:36,310 --> 00:08:38,470
You ever seen a limb come out of a cast?

103
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:40,570
You ever seen that?

104
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:42,880
It's icky, isn't it?

105
00:08:43,810 --> 00:08:44,730
It's thin.

106
00:08:45,450 --> 00:08:46,490
It's scaly.

107
00:08:47,070 --> 00:08:48,390
It's atrophied.

108
00:08:48,990 --> 00:08:50,070
It's stiff.

109
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:55,040
And you have to work it slowly and build the muscle back up.

110
00:08:55,040 --> 00:09:00,040
And that repetitive motion, the doing and the squeezing and the lifting and all of those things,

111
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:04,160
build that muscle tissue back up strong once again.

112
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:10,400
Well, you know, friends, praise grows stronger as well as we exercise it.

113
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:14,740
The more that we do it, we're flexing and building that muscle.

114
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,320
And we're doing it to honor our Lord.

115
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:22,420
How can we not want to exercise and sweat and push and press for our Lord?

116
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:29,920
And so one of the ways that we praise, one of the biblical ways we praise, is through song.

117
00:09:31,330 --> 00:09:32,070
Why song?

118
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:34,330
I've thought about that a number of different times.

119
00:09:34,330 --> 00:09:41,220
Why is it that around the world the people of God praise and give God glory and extol Him?

120
00:09:41,220 --> 00:09:52,440
why through song? What is it about song that is so important for people to do? I think because songs

121
00:09:52,440 --> 00:10:01,890
do two things at once. The text and the words and the meanings of songs touch our heads. They allow

122
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:13,110
us to express our thoughts, but the music feeds our souls and our hearts. Songs mean things to us

123
00:10:13,110 --> 00:10:16,730
on different levels, head and heart, at the same time.

124
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,300
I think that's why God wants us to sing a new song,

125
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:26,000
because it ministers to our head and our hearts,

126
00:10:26,220 --> 00:10:30,380
and we give to God from our head and our hearts at the same time.

127
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,570
Donald Hustad said in Leadership Magazine,

128
00:10:34,570 --> 00:10:39,690
Somehow, about 40% of churchgoers seem to have picked up the idea

129
00:10:39,690 --> 00:10:42,710
that singing in church is for the singers.

130
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:47,740
And he says the truth is, singing is for believers.

131
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:54,940
The relevant question is not, do you have a voice, but do you have a song?

132
00:10:56,890 --> 00:10:57,930
That's for all of us.

133
00:10:58,590 --> 00:10:59,590
That's for all of us.

134
00:11:00,210 --> 00:11:01,610
You may not be trained.

135
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:03,030
You may not have vibrato.

136
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:04,290
You may not have falsetto.

137
00:11:04,510 --> 00:11:06,150
You may not have proper breathing.

138
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:11,710
You may not have all those things, but it doesn't matter to the Lord

139
00:11:11,710 --> 00:11:15,470
because he wants your head and your heart as you give him a song,

140
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:18,990
as squeaky and gravelly or beautiful and polished.

141
00:11:19,150 --> 00:11:20,050
It doesn't matter.

142
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:21,590
It blesses the Lord.

143
00:11:23,180 --> 00:11:28,840
And so friends, if you're self-conscious about the person in front of you, don't worry about it.

144
00:11:30,260 --> 00:11:31,760
Not your problem.

145
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,240
It's not their problem.

146
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,950
Because God wants to hear you give from your head and your heart.

147
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:38,720
Can you do that?

148
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:39,600
All of us.

149
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:43,100
As a way to worship and give Him praise.

150
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:47,730
Do you desire a greater life of praise?

151
00:11:47,930 --> 00:11:49,050
Then we have to practice.

152
00:11:49,930 --> 00:11:55,150
If we're going to practice and stretch and flex that muscle, we have to be here, friends.

153
00:11:55,150 --> 00:12:04,510
here's my challenge. Please come to worship. I know that sounds basic. That sounds like baby

154
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:13,740
steps. I know. But in our highly mobile culture, in our highly choice-riddled culture, it's so easy

155
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:18,240
to skip here and there. And you know what happens? You're here one every four to six weeks.

156
00:12:19,640 --> 00:12:24,360
And if you really want to be in a habit of praising, it's hard to corporately praise

157
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,580
when you're not here.

158
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:29,790
If I'm offending you, I'm sorry.

159
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:31,110
I'm just trying to tell you in my heart,

160
00:12:31,530 --> 00:12:32,650
we need to be here.

161
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:35,470
You need to be here, and others need you to be here.

162
00:12:36,090 --> 00:12:38,350
Because when you're not here, somebody else loses.

163
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:38,990
Do you know that?

164
00:12:39,570 --> 00:12:41,590
Your presence blesses somebody else.

165
00:12:41,590 --> 00:12:43,650
You may not know who you're affecting,

166
00:12:45,530 --> 00:12:46,830
but you're affecting somebody

167
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:48,350
by your presence and your absence.

168
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,520
And we need to make worship a priority.

169
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:54,550
And I know it's countercultural.

170
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:56,670
And the neighbors are getting up,

171
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:57,970
and they got their jogging suits on.

172
00:12:57,970 --> 00:12:58,610
And they've got the dogs.

173
00:12:58,690 --> 00:13:01,070
They're going to the park and the beach and racquetball and tennis.

174
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:02,070
I know all those things.

175
00:13:02,110 --> 00:13:04,430
They're going surfing and Disney and all that stuff.

176
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:06,430
And you get up, get in your car, and you head to church.

177
00:13:06,650 --> 00:13:08,630
It's bizarre, I know.

178
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:14,420
We're in a culture that does not understand anymore what you're doing here.

179
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:18,940
But God has called you to be here.

180
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:21,870
And he wants you to be here.

181
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:26,430
Not to manipulate you because he wants to bless you.

182
00:13:26,830 --> 00:13:28,860
And he wants you to bless him.

183
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,280
And that happens when the church gathers together.

184
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:37,340
And so I want us to see this time not as just a routine that's hollow

185
00:13:37,340 --> 00:13:40,220
because we just do it every seven days,

186
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,320
but because we're here to meet with our God.

187
00:13:46,570 --> 00:13:47,590
So please come.

188
00:13:48,250 --> 00:13:49,890
Enter into the life of praise.

189
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:53,220
Sing unto God with all of your being.

190
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:57,840
Give God thanks in your quiet times at home with him.

191
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:01,450
And when you're praying, give him praise.

192
00:14:01,830 --> 00:14:04,590
Sing a song in the Lord to the Lord in your car.

193
00:14:05,810 --> 00:14:10,030
Sing a song on the way to church to prepare your heart for corporate worship together.

194
00:14:11,090 --> 00:14:15,850
There's lots of ways that you can begin a life of faithful praise.

195
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:18,790
And friends, I will put this test out there.

196
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:24,690
If you come and worship God and give Him your heart and really seek to honor Him over six months,

197
00:14:24,810 --> 00:14:27,410
I trust you will be a different person.

198
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:30,280
Try it.

199
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:37,880
Psalm 95 says,

200
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:40,500
Come, let us sing to the Lord.

201
00:14:41,550 --> 00:14:44,790
Let us give a joyous shout to the rock of our salvation.

202
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:47,730
Let us come before him with thanksgiving.

203
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:53,460
Let us sing him psalms of praise, for the Lord is a great God.

204
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:58,620
The great King above all gods, he owns the depths of the earth,

205
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:01,800
and even the mightiest mountains are his.

206
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:06,200
The sea belongs to him, for he made it.

207
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:09,380
His hands formed the dry land too.

208
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:12,820
Come, let us worship and bow down.

209
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:18,040
Let us kneel before the Lord, our maker, for he is our God.

210
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:22,920
We are the people he watches over, the sheep under his care.

211
00:15:25,260 --> 00:15:31,740
The habit of praise, the lifestyle of praise, strengthens and renews our faith.

212
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:33,880
Faith is fed by worship.

213
00:15:35,030 --> 00:15:39,370
We welcome you to come and grow your faith as you grow in worship.

214
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:42,860
Number two, the lessons of praise.

215
00:15:43,420 --> 00:15:46,410
The lessons of praise shape our perspective.

216
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:53,110
When we come and give God praise, when we come and give him adoration,

217
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:56,290
we put life back into perspective, don't we?

218
00:15:56,290 --> 00:16:03,880
We realize when we give God glory and praise, we realize he is God and I am not.

219
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:10,300
We put things back into perspective that he is in control and we are not.

220
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:13,910
All of our life management is still an illusion

221
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:16,830
because God is ultimately the one in control.

222
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,640
We can try and shape things and we can do a decent job,

223
00:16:21,740 --> 00:16:23,100
but ultimately God is in control.

224
00:16:23,220 --> 00:16:24,480
He is God and we are not.

225
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:27,760
And through praise, we remember that reality.

226
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,840
Despite all the busyness in our lives,

227
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:32,560
all the hurry, all the stress,

228
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:34,540
all the suffocating tyranny of the urgent,

229
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:38,180
through praise, we realize that God is God

230
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,980
and that brings us into a place of peace

231
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:42,300
and allows us to rest.

232
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,100
And put life into perspective again.

233
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:46,220
We need that.

234
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:50,520
We need that every few days to remember who's in charge of life.

235
00:16:51,590 --> 00:16:52,430
And to give us peace.

236
00:16:52,830 --> 00:16:56,710
The Bible says in Psalm 46.10, great short sentence, says it all.

237
00:16:57,050 --> 00:17:01,260
Be still and know that I am God.

238
00:17:02,870 --> 00:17:03,370
Be still.

239
00:17:05,780 --> 00:17:07,220
We're in a busy culture, friends.

240
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:08,460
We're in a loud culture.

241
00:17:08,940 --> 00:17:12,500
And we need to draw away and be still.

242
00:17:13,860 --> 00:17:16,460
And through praise and worship, we know that he is God.

243
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,860
A poet once wrote this.

244
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:22,850
We mutter, we sputter, we fume and we spurt.

245
00:17:23,780 --> 00:17:26,680
We mumble and grumble, our feelings get hurt.

246
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:30,970
We can't understand things, our vision grows dim,

247
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:35,510
when all that we need is a moment with him.

248
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:37,860
Amen is right.

249
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,360
It says it all, doesn't it?

250
00:17:40,490 --> 00:17:43,010
Worship puts things back into perspective.

251
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:47,150
A lifestyle of praise, both privately and corporately,

252
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:50,250
It gives our souls the proper perspective about life.

253
00:17:50,890 --> 00:17:55,710
Through worship, friends, we learn to fret less and desire God more.

254
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:59,010
Eugene Peterson said this.

255
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:02,550
He said, worship does not satisfy our hunger for God.

256
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:04,370
It wets our appetite.

257
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,780
Do you want to know God more?

258
00:18:08,460 --> 00:18:10,700
Do you want to have more hunger for Him?

259
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:14,300
The more we worship, the more we give praise to God,

260
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:16,620
the more we desire to know God more fully,

261
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:20,700
the more we crave his power and his presence in our lives.

262
00:18:24,490 --> 00:18:27,830
I've found that when we praise more, we hold on to life a little more loosely.

263
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:32,420
Through praise and worship, we're reminded that everything is God's.

264
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:39,500
We realize our lives, our homes, our jobs, our money, our problems, our stresses, our worries,

265
00:18:39,940 --> 00:18:41,980
all of it is God's.

266
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:47,890
And those realities come together when we sing and praise and worship.

267
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,720
Psalm 24 becomes our anthem.

268
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:58,340
The earth is the Lord's, and everything in it, the world and all its people belong to Him.

269
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:04,220
For He laid the earth's foundation on the seas and built it on the ocean's depths.

270
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:06,800
It's all His.

271
00:19:07,870 --> 00:19:10,530
Coming together in worship, we put that into perspective.

272
00:19:12,220 --> 00:19:13,320
Friends, do you need encouragement?

273
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:15,660
Seek God through praise.

274
00:19:17,180 --> 00:19:18,840
Does your worldview need adjusting?

275
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,360
Enter God's presence through worship and praise.

276
00:19:24,210 --> 00:19:26,370
Do you need to let go of some things in your life?

277
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:32,600
Come and grab onto the corporate worship of God and let some things go.

278
00:19:34,170 --> 00:19:35,750
Do you need more of God in your life?

279
00:19:37,100 --> 00:19:38,920
Pursue him through praise.

280
00:19:40,830 --> 00:19:43,230
You see, the lessons of praise, they shape our perspective.

281
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:49,580
And finally, the power of praise, it energizes our conduct.

282
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:57,860
One reality that we need to remember is that a life mimics what you worship.

283
00:19:58,940 --> 00:20:02,000
What you worship is what you become like.

284
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:07,900
If you worship superficial things, your life becomes superficial.

285
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:10,600
Have you seen that around you?

286
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:14,960
When people worship the things that really don't matter,

287
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,440
their lives take on that character quality as well.

288
00:20:19,460 --> 00:20:22,480
If you worship perverted things, your life becomes perverted.

289
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:25,120
If you worship evil things, your life becomes evil.

290
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:29,630
If you worship the true God, your life becomes godly.

291
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:36,860
And so coming and praising and worshiping shapes us and changes us

292
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:41,660
and energizes our conduct as we try and be more like Jesus.

293
00:20:43,310 --> 00:20:48,530
A big part of our spiritual walk, a big part of our Christian faith is our spiritual formation.

294
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:54,760
Spiritual formation is a term whereby a process, we become more and more like Jesus

295
00:20:54,760 --> 00:21:00,420
in our character, in our attitude, in our power, in our perspective.

296
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:03,820
it's a multi-dimensional process

297
00:21:03,820 --> 00:21:05,890
but we are consciously

298
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:07,990
saying we want to be more

299
00:21:07,990 --> 00:21:09,170
like Jesus Christ

300
00:21:09,170 --> 00:21:13,230
and forming our spirits

301
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:15,930
is a process we enter into by the Holy Spirit

302
00:21:15,930 --> 00:21:17,690
whereby in our lives

303
00:21:17,690 --> 00:21:19,670
and through others shaping and molding

304
00:21:19,670 --> 00:21:21,550
us we take on the character

305
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,470
and the qualities of our Lord

306
00:21:23,470 --> 00:21:25,900
and praise

307
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:28,320
allows us to nourish

308
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:31,840
the Spirit's movement in our lives

309
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,940
in Galatians 5

310
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:37,720
22. Many of you know this. Just a wonderful description

311
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:41,860
of what happens when the Spirit controls our lives. He says, Paul says,

312
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:46,060
when the Holy Spirit controls our lives, He will produce this kind

313
00:21:46,060 --> 00:21:49,810
of fruit in us. Love, joy,

314
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:54,120
peace, patience, kindness,

315
00:21:55,420 --> 00:21:57,780
goodness, faithfulness,

316
00:21:58,660 --> 00:22:04,040
gentleness, and self-control. We want to know

317
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:05,980
what a believer in Jesus looks like?

318
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,860
They're a person filled with love and joy

319
00:22:09,860 --> 00:22:13,840
and peace and patience and so on.

320
00:22:16,030 --> 00:22:17,550
The more we praise God,

321
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:20,950
the more our heart becomes open to being loving.

322
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:25,120
The more I give my life to the Lord through praise,

323
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:28,000
the more I sense the joy of the Lord.

324
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:32,560
The more I offer up to God my love and affirmation of Him,

325
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:35,820
the more I'm able to sense His peace in my life.

326
00:22:35,820 --> 00:22:44,830
The more I touch God's heart through praise, the more my heart becomes patient with others.

327
00:22:46,170 --> 00:22:47,110
And on and on it goes.

328
00:22:48,170 --> 00:22:52,970
The more we praise, the more we surrender our lives and give God all that he's due,

329
00:22:53,730 --> 00:22:58,390
the more our character becomes shaped like this in the fruit of the Spirit.

330
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:05,240
And so through praise and worship, my life becomes a field that's ready for the Lord to plow it up

331
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:09,980
and plant seed and allow those seeds to grow into the fruit of the Spirit.

332
00:23:09,980 --> 00:23:13,850
and the more that we're open then to the farmer

333
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:16,690
harvesting these fruits in us.

334
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:23,090
The power of praise, it energizes and fuels our conduct.

335
00:23:24,610 --> 00:23:27,670
And so in conclusion, before we do some praising and worshiping,

336
00:23:28,130 --> 00:23:31,950
are you ready, church, for more of the Lord in your life?

337
00:23:33,640 --> 00:23:34,120
Are you ready?

338
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:37,820
Are you ready for more of the Lord's power and presence

339
00:23:37,820 --> 00:23:40,740
here at this place, at this church,

340
00:23:41,140 --> 00:23:42,740
on Sundays and Wednesdays

341
00:23:42,740 --> 00:23:44,740
and when we gather as the body together?

342
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:51,160
If you're ready, then lift up your praise today, for he is worthy.

343
00:23:52,260 --> 00:23:53,840
Praise the Lord.

344
00:23:55,530 --> 00:23:56,350
David, would you lead us?

